{
  "text": "As mentioned earlier, the inverse hysteresis model has the same number of backlash operators as the hysteresis model, i.e., N=10. Using [CITATION_1] and (10) The results of AFM imaging using the two different models are shown in Fig. 9 and Fig. 10 . Note that, the AFM image obtained without a feedforward controller (as shown in Fig. 2) , has distorted length. That is to say, the widths and intervals of these grids seem unequal in Fig. 2 , where in reality, they are in fact equal. However, when the model-based feedforward controller is implemented, as shown in Fig. 9 (based on symmetric model) and Fig. 10 (based on asymmetric model) , the widths and intervals become equal visually.",
